    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="587"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d587">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/834.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Smith</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 12, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Diplomatic Corps notified by Haitian Government of the blockade of Cape Haitien
                    by a Haitian war vessel. Matter discussed by Diplomatic Corps, which will await
                    the action of the Government of the United States. German Minister is disposed
                    to recognize the blockade as effective but will not act at once.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
